.Dd July 2025
.Dt MORIARTY 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm moriarty
.Nd an assistant for an assistant \(em Claude Code and pi log analysis, cost or token reporting, and tool call permissioning
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Cm api\-pricing
.Fl d Ar dir
.Op Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
.Op Fl \-conversations
.Op Fl \-tokens
.Op Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
.Op Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
.Nm
.Cm graphs claude
.Fl d Ar dir
.Op Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
.Op Fl \-conversations
.Op Fl \-tokens
.Op Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
.Op Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
.Nm
.Cm graphs pi
.Op Fl d Ar dir
.Op Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
.Op Fl \-conversations
.Op Fl \-tokens
.Op Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
.Op Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
.Nm
.Cm pi cost
.Op Fl d Ar dir
.Op Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
.Op Fl \-conversations
.Op Fl \-tokens
.Op Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
.Op Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
.Nm
.Cm mcp
.Ar server
.Nm
.Cm approve\-project
.Ar project_dir
.Nm
.Cm hooks exec
.Nm
.Cm test project\-tools
.Op Ar project_dir
.Nm
.Cm test checks
.Op Ar project_dir
.Nm
.Cm test bash\-rules
.Op Fl c Ar config
.Op Fl \-json
.Op Ar command
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a Rust CLI tool for working with Claude Code and pi session logs.
It provides API and pi usage analysis, chart-focused graph commands,
MCP servers, and a security hook system for controlling which tools
and commands Claude Code can execute.
.Ss API Pricing
The
.Cm api\-pricing
subcommand analyzes Claude API usage from log directories
and generates detailed cost or token-count reports.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl d , Fl \-dir Ar dir
Directory to analyze for API usage.
.It Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
Timezone for date determination.
Default:
.Ar local .
.It Fl \-conversations
Aggregate by conversation/session instead of by date.
.It Fl \-tokens
Show token counts instead of dollar costs.
.It Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
Start time filter in ISO 8601 format
.Pq e.g., 2025\-01\-01T00:00:00Z .
UTC is assumed if no timezone is specified.
.It Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
End time filter in ISO 8601 format.
.El
.Ss Pi Cost
The
.Cm pi cost
subcommand analyzes pi session logs and generates either cost reports
or token-count reports using the same date and conversation grouping options
as
.Cm api\-pricing .
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl d , Fl \-dir Ar dir
Directory to analyze for pi session usage.
Default:
.Pa ~/.pi/agent/sessions .
.It Fl \-timezone Ar local|utc
Timezone for date determination.
Default:
.Ar local .
.It Fl \-conversations
Aggregate by conversation/session instead of by date.
.It Fl \-tokens
Show token counts instead of dollar costs.
.It Fl \-start\-time Ar DATETIME
Start time filter in ISO 8601 format.
UTC is assumed if no timezone is specified.
.It Fl \-end\-time Ar DATETIME
End time filter in ISO 8601 format.
.El
.Ss Graphs
The
.Cm graphs claude
and
.Cm graphs pi
subcommands render chart-focused stacked summaries for Claude/API and pi usage.
They accept the same timezone, conversation, token, and time-filter flags
as the corresponding table reports.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm graphs claude Fl d Ar dir
Render Claude/API usage graphs from the given log directory.
.It Cm graphs pi Op Fl d Ar dir
Render pi usage graphs from the given session directory.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.pi/agent/sessions
when
.Fl \-dir
is omitted.
.El
.Ss MCP Servers
The
.Cm mcp
subcommand runs one of the built\-in Model Context Protocol servers
for git operations and project tools.
.Ss Project Approval
The
.Cm approve\-project
subcommand opens a TUI to approve project tools
defined in
.Pa .config/tools.toml
for MCP server execution.
.Ss Hooks
The
.Cm hooks exec
subcommand executes Claude Code hooks, reading input from stdin
and applying configured tool and bash rules.
This is the entry point used by Claude Code's hook system.
.Ss Test Commands
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm test project\-tools Op Ar project_dir
Run all configured project tools in parallel.
Defaults to the current directory.
.It Cm test checks Op Ar project_dir
Run all configured project checks in parallel.
.It Cm test bash\-rules Op Ar command
Test a bash command against configured rules.
If no command is provided, reads from stdin.
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl c , Fl \-config Ar path
Custom config file path.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml .
.It Fl \-json
Output results as JSON instead of pretty\-printed text.
.El
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ev XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for configuration files.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.config .
.It Ev XDG_STATE_HOME
Base directory for state files including logs.
Defaults to
.Pa ~/.local/state .
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa ~/.config/moriarty/tool_rules.toml
Tool and bash rules configuration file.
See
.Xr moriarty\-tool\-rules 5
and
.Xr moriarty\-bash\-rules 5 .
.It Pa ~/.local/state/moriarty/logs/
Runtime log directory.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr moriarty\-tool\-rules 5 ,
.Xr moriarty\-bash\-rules 5
